file_content.text: The Empire is tightening its grip on Nar Shaddaa, thanks to you.
I'm filing a report to Admiral Ange. The operation was a resounding success. The Republic's power base here is obliterated.
They know we crippled them, of course--but they can't prove it. The Empire waged war and maintained the illusion of peace.
No thanks to you! How dare you authorize the Shadow Syndicate's attack on that Republic transport!
If you lack the conviction to destroy our enemies, you should return to Korriban for further training.
I acted as a Sith. Can you?
You arrogant.... You've no idea the consequences of your actions.
Fear creates weakness. Weakness leaves our enemy vulnerable.
Terror is our goal here.
The Republic isn't feeling fear. It feels anger--and anger grants strength.
I don't need your permission to do my job.
I dare all sorts of things.
Dozens of hunters vanish in Imperial space every year. You'd be wise to remember that.
Time was of the essence. It seemed the best course of action.
A decision had to be made.
I expect better from Imperial Intelligence. Clearly, standards are falling.
It was an unmarked warship. I thought the point was to drive the Republic away for good.
You disapprove, Zavrasha?
Publicly slaughtering people gives the Republic martyrs to rally around. You haven't weakened them--you've strengthened their resolve.
Watch your mouth, or you'll be shopping for a cybernetic jaw replacement.
Don't snap at me--or else.
Don't threaten me. My master could crush you with a flick of the wrist.
You jeopardized everything for a childish prank. The Dark Council will not be pleased.
The Dark Council is pleased. Our success on a densely populated world means we can do it anywhere. Your service has been most illuminating.
Tell the Dark Council that victory is within our reach. We need only to seize it.
The Empire will win the war.
Consider that message delivered.
I'm always seeking new venues to show the weak just how powerless they are.
It was my pleasure.
Considering our success here, I'm sure more opportunities will come.
I didn't do this for your illumination.
You're welcome. Pay me.
I'll leave your reward to Colonel Harok. He handles the administrative duties.
No need for thanks, my lord. It was an honor to serve.
It was my duty to a superior.
Your professionalism is exemplary--and will be remembered.
I'd be happy to give you a private report on the battle, my lord.
[Flirt] Celebrate, Zavrasha?
Carry on, Colonel. My ship is docked nearby....
Those were most revealing details. I'm glad you shared them.
I'd hate for your knowledge to be incomplete.
Me, too.
I think there's more to learn--but we'll have to wait for another time.
My pleasure--but we both have business elsewhere.
It's time for us to part.
Farewell, then. Colonel Harok will see to your other compensation.
I should've known it was a mistake when you refused to dim the lights.
That was a waste of time.
Few men survive insulting me. Consider yourself lucky.
I can't speak for my friends, but if you require anything else, I'm happy to help.
[Flirt] Anytime, Zavrasha.
Someone should be flattered by that offer. Go find her.
What other populated worlds is the Empire planning to invade?
Where else will we attack?
If you're needed, you will know.
My master has requested I return to Dromund Kaas. I depart immediately. Perhaps we'll see each other again....
Thank you, as well... for contributing absolutely nothing of value.
Enough of your condescension.
You should be more careful. Politics are more dangerous than any battlefield.
You led the Empire to a significant victory, and should be rewarded for it.
If you're planning any more battles, don't hesitate to call.
Thank you, Colonel.
You'll be the first to know.
I can't wait to see what you have for me. Maybe the middle of the spaceport isn't the best place for it?
[Flirt] A private gift?
I... ahem... the admiral expects my report... but he wouldn't begrudge me some respite after this great victory....
I'd forgotten how it feels to just take some time off and relax. Thank you for reminding me.
I knew there was more to you than that uniform.
It was a pleasure.
Yes, well... ahem. I am back on duty.
What good is crushing the enemy if you can't savor the moment?
You're welcome.
Perhaps someday we'll celebrate our total victory.
Playtime's over. The admiral is waiting.
Get back to work.
You're right, of course. I should finish my report to Admiral Ange immediately. Farewell.
Ah... ahem... I'm only able to provide what my superior has authorized.
Speaking only for myself, I think we make an outstanding team. Do you have any other emergencies that might require my attention?
[Flirt] Let's keep working.
I, ah... that is... not at this time. Thank you for offering.
I risked more than I bargained for on this mission.
No arguments there.
I hope the compensation is adequate.
I must remain here and complete my report to Admiral Ange. Farewell.
Do the galaxy a favor and stop talking. I'd rather listen to mynocks breed.
Just hand it over and shut up.
Take your payment. Goodbye.
We cannot let the Republic dominate us on this world. Coordinate with our strike team to destroy the enemy's advances.
Colonel Harok. I'm here under orders from Admiral Jefand Ange.
The admiral was impressed with your handling of that revolution in the Duros Sector. Word is you saved him from a Gen'Dai.
The creature thought it was unstoppable. It found out differently.
Yes, "the Flame."
We hope you'll prove equally effective against a much larger target.
Why isn't the admiral communicating with me personally?
Where is the admiral?
He intends no disrespect. He's in counsel with high-ranking members of the Hutt Cartel's leadership.
If you want an autograph, ask. Otherwise, stop wasting time.
Get to the point.
I was merely attempting to provide some context.
Admiral Ange's mission is to secure the Empire's interests here. Many factions are seeking to take what's rightfully ours.
There should be fewer of those factions these days. I made sure of it.
I've eliminated many enemies.
Unfortunately, the ones that remain aren't so easily swept aside.
Nar Shaddaa is neutral territory. We have no claim to this world.
This isn't our land.
On the contrary, one day all of this will be ours. Best not tell the Hutts, of course.
Considering all the threats I've had to deal with here, the admiral isn't doing a very good job.
Your boss should work harder.
He's only recently arrived. His predecessor was recalled to Dromund Kaas--permanently.
Admiral Ange has discovered an opportunity to cripple the Republic and expand our control over this world--but we must act swiftly.
So swiftly you'd start without me? Zavrasha--apprentice to Darth Mortis of the Dark Council. Charmed.
All I want to hear is how we're going to drive the Republic off Nar Shaddaa.
Skip the pleasantries.
I admire single-mindedness. Let's hope you can take direction.
Why have I been listening to this talking uniform, when I could've been chatting with a beautiful creature like you?
[Flirt] Likewise.
Don't invite what you're ill-equipped to handle.
If you wish to continue this briefing, I'm all ears.
A pleasure to meet you.
I wouldn't deny Harok his spotlight. You know men and their egos.
No offense, but you make my skin crawl.
I don't like looking at you.
I strive to have an impact on everyone I meet.
Lord Zavrasha is here at her master's request. She's ensuring our operation doesn't endanger the Emperor's treaty with the Republic.
We must preserve the illusion of peace and safeguard our dominion on Nar Shaddaa... while burning the Republic's holdings to the ground.
May this inferno spread to Coruscant itself.
A glorious vision.
A poet. Who could've known Darth Baras was a patron of the arts?
It's about time we ended those insufferable fools.
And their citizens, too.
Hypocrites. Always prattling about peace as they prepare for war.
Flamethrower fuel's expensive, lady. How much torching can you afford?
Burning costs extra.
Ignite the right target and a blaze will spread on its own.
I admire discretion. Strike from the shadows, leave the enemy powerless.
An excellent plan.
I'm relieved someone understands the need for delicacy.
Why deny the truth? Let them fear the Empire's might.
Do we have to keep it secret?
We're laying the foundation for future conquests. We must be patient, as when we first returned to enemy space.
Let's not waste any time. We have infernos to light.
I do enjoy a good fire.
These flames must be controlled, so we may occupy our foe's territory once the vermin are gone.
Ahem. Imperial allies in the Hutt Cartel have revealed the location of a Republic research complex where the enemy develops advanced battlefield technologies.
Heavily armed troops and Jedi guard the complex. Unless we destroy it, their technology will overwhelm us when the final war begins.
Our Hutt friends have manufactured a communications blackout so we may annihilate the Republic threat undetected. But that window of opportunity is brief.
The enemy isn't prepared for war--but we are. They won't have time to contemplate their pathetic deaths.
We're always ready to strike.
Let them experience at least a brief moment of terror. It's rewarding.
I learned to kill efficiently on Korriban. The trick is slaughtering the next foe while the last one's still dying.
I won't need long.
Yes, timing is everything.
Whenever I need a new window, I just punch through a wall.
I can always blast an opening.
Your home must be well ventilated.
I was previously assigned to Hutta, my lord. Free assistance from the Hutts should be considered highly suspect.
Beware of help from the Hutts.
Those bloated sacks of filth know who they should side with. Better to be the Empire's friend than its enemy.
I understand how the Empire benefits from this attack. What about me?
How will I be compensated?
Nar Shaddaa doesn't lack for expensive accessories. We'll find something to suit your tastes.
Bad timing for me. I was just leaving the planet.
Sorry, I can't help you.
What could be more important than securing the Empire's future? Shall we entrust this battle to lesser warriors?
Never leave victory to chance--or amateurs. I'm in.
That would be disastrous.
I'll never hear the end of this if I leave. Tell me the plan.
Your guilt-trip worked.
That's the spirit. I'd hate to inform my master of your cowardice.
Go to these coordinates. Captain Westro is standing by to explain your mission objectives inside the research complex.
Exterminate everything. Leave scorched ground behind.
Easy. Destroy it all, right?
Close, but you'll also have allies inside. Work with them and focus your efforts.
I look forward to celebrating with you later, Colonel.
[Flirt] We'll meet again, sir.
I... ah... of course.
You look like you know your way around a battlefield. Care to join in?
You aren't coming?
My orders are to remain here and coordinate the admiral's strike team.
This conversation tested the limits of my patience.
Finally! I'm getting bored.
I'll be monitoring your progress. I expect great things.
Good hunting. Let's show the Republic its days are numbered.
You'll just have to make do.
I'm going now. [Refuse quest]
The Dark Council will know of your refusal.
If you'll excuse me, I must report to Admiral Ange. He was counting on your assistance.
A pleasure to see you, my lord.
I have no need of your services.
Good to see you, agent.
